BEGIN:VEVENT
DESCRIPTION:How pleasant it is when the people of tech come together in unity!\n\nAfter a year of talking about it\, we’re finally doing it: a chill summer cookout for everyone in Baltimore tech. No booths\, no buzzwords — just food\, sun\, and a mic for any group that wants to say hi.\n\nWe are hoping to cultivate a virtuous environment of Baltimore's best tech leaders\, to share organizational tips\, and to lean into Smalltimore's unique social strengths in building the future economy. Ultimately\, we hope to foster the relationships that create better lives for ourselves and our people.\n\nParticipating groups\n\n• Code Collective\n• Baltimore Node Makerspace\n• Baltimore Tech\n• Brady UX\n• DevOps Columbia\n• Blk Tech Connect\n• Baltimore Indie Game Devs\n\nFree admission. Food will be provided!\n\nThe event will occur at Wonderground Park in collaboration with the Greenmount West Community Association. It's nearby Guilford Hall Brewery\, home of EquiTech Tuesday and occasional host of Baltimore Rhythm Festival.\n\nIn the case of inclement weather\, the event will occur at Mount Vernon Marketplace\, or at a local bar.\n\nEvent Link: https://www.meetup.com/code-collective/events/307426667/
DTEND:20250628T190000Z
LOCATION:Wonderground Park\, 409 E Lanvale St\, Baltimore\, MD 21202\, Baltimore\, MD us
DTSTART:20250628T170000Z
SUMMARY:Tech Unity Cookout
UID:9f8f7001-3a38-424c-9e81-fe2aba21f789@9f8f.org
URL:https://www.meetup.com/code-collective/events/307426667/
END:VEVENT
