BEGIN:VEVENT
DESCRIPTION:Our Demo Day is a chance for members of the local tech community to show off the cool projects they’ve been working on. Come and enjoy our participant’s ten minute demos with five minutes for questions.\n\nWe'll have demos on 3D Structural Optimization\, GTM partnership automation and more.\n\nAfter the demos\, each of the participants will have their own table for you to ask more questions about their work in depth. After 30 mins of this\, we will have a vote for the winner.\n\nSCHEDULE:\nNetworking - 11:00am-11:30am\nDemos - 11:30am-12:30pm\nTable Talk - 12:30pm-1:00pm\nVote 1:00pm-1:10pm\nNetworking - 1:10pm - 2:00pm\n\nVenue:\nDigital Harbor Foundation\n1045 Light St. Baltimore\, MD 21230\n\nPARKING: There is metered street parking. If all else fails\, park at the West Street Garage. Residents of Baltimore near Charles St should consider the free Charm City Circulator bus.\n\nHOW TO FIND US\nPlease use the main door at 1045 Light Street. If the door is closed\, please ring the doorbell.\n\nEvent Link: https://www.meetup.com/baltimore-code-and-coffee/events/307627099/
DTEND:20250614T180000Z
LOCATION:Digital Harbor Foundation Tech Center\, 1045 Light St\, Baltimore\, MD us
DTSTART:20250614T150000Z
